Class Authentication

class

Authentication

classdesc

The constructor of the Authentication object. This object is used for authenticating a user to Sitefinity.

param

An object containing configuration options for the Authentication object.

param

Your service url that points to the configured instance of Sitefinity service.

login

  • login(username: string, password: string, success: any, failure: any): void
    • Defined in Authentication.ts:30

    Logins the user. A service call is made to login the user. If the call is successful and the service returns a token, this token is cached in the Authentication object.

    memberof

    Authentication

    instance
    deprecated

    This method is deprecated and should not be used with versions of sitefinity >= 10.0

    example

    sf.authentication.login("username", "password", successCb, failureCb);
